definitions: person who supervises students during examinations to prevent cheating
official at some universities responsible for maintaining discipline and standards
examples: The proctor walked between the rows checking for unauthorized materials
Students must remain silent while the proctor distributes exam papers
The university proctor investigated allegations of academic misconduct last semester
She met with the proctor to discuss the dormitory noise complaints

definitions: process of finding and acquiring goods, services, or works from external sources
examples: The procurement department negotiated better prices with suppliers this quarter
Government procurement policies must ensure fair competition among vendors

definitions: pointed stick or tool used for poking or stirring things
gentle push or reminder intended to prompt action or response
examples: The farmer used a prod to guide cattle into the barn
She gave the fire a prod with the metal poker
His mother's prod finally got him to clean his messy room
The deadline served as a prod to complete the project

definitions: person who spends money or resources freely and recklessly without thought for the future
examples: The prodigal heir squandered his inheritance within two years
Like the biblical prodigal, he returned home after wasting everything

definitions: young person with exceptional abilities or qualities, especially in a particular field
examples: The chess prodigy defeated grandmasters before his tenth birthday
Mozart was a musical prodigy who composed symphonies as a child

definitions: informal shortened form of professor used in casual speech or writing
examples: The prof announced that the midterm would cover five chapters
Students lined up outside the prof's office during consultation hours

definitions: language that is considered offensive, blasphemous, or shows disrespect particularly regarding religious matters
examples: The movie rating warned viewers about violence and profanity throughout
He apologized for the profanity that slipped out during the meeting

definitions: act of claiming or declaring something openly, especially beliefs, feelings, or intentions
examples: His professing of innocence didn't convince the skeptical jury members
The professing of faith is central to many religious ceremonies

definitions: skill, good judgment, and polite behavior expected from a person trained to do a job well
examples: Her professionalism impressed clients during the difficult contract negotiations
The company values professionalism and requires appropriate dress code daily

definitions: position or rank of professor at a college or university, including associated duties and privileges
examples: She accepted a professorship at the prestigious research university last year
The endowed professorship comes with generous funding for academic research

definitions: high degree of skill or expertise in a particular area or activity
examples: The job requires proficiency in at least two programming languages
Her proficiency in Spanish helped secure the international business deal

definitions: process of analyzing and recording someone's psychological and behavioral characteristics
practice of categorizing people based on observed characteristics often in discriminatory ways
examples: Criminal profiling helped investigators narrow down their list of suspects

Airport security faced criticism for profiling passengers based on appearance

definitions: ability of a business or activity to generate profit relative to its expenses over time
examples: The company's profitability improved after implementing cost reduction measures
Investors closely monitor quarterly reports to assess long-term profitability

definitions: abundance or large quantity of something, especially when it appears extravagant or excessive
examples: Spring brought a profusion of wildflowers to the mountain meadows
The buffet table displayed a profusion of delicious international dishes

definitions: direct ancestor or originator of a person, animal, plant, or idea from which others develop
examples: DNA testing revealed that wolves were the progenitors of domestic dogs
The philosopher is considered the progenitor of modern democratic theory

definitions: descendants or offspring of a person, animal, or plant considered as a group
examples: The scientist studied three generations of progeny from the original specimens
The wealthy patriarch divided his estate equally among all his progeny

definitions: sign or indication of how a situation will develop, especially regarding medical conditions
examples: Dark clouds on the horizon were a prognostic of approaching storms
The doctor explained that test results were a positive prognostic

definitions: process of writing instructions for computers to execute specific tasks
act of scheduling or planning events, broadcasts, or activities in advance
examples: She spent hours programing the new mobile application features yesterday
The programing course teaches students fundamental coding concepts and practices
The festival programing includes concerts, workshops, and art exhibitions daily
Television programing changes seasonally to attract different audience demographics

definitions: planned series of activities, events, or procedures with a particular purpose
television or radio show broadcast as part of a regular schedule
examples: The conference programme includes keynote speeches and networking sessions
The training programme lasts six months with weekly progress evaluations
The nature programme about arctic wildlife won several documentary awards
She never misses her favorite cooking programme on Saturday mornings

definitions: person who writes and tests code to create software applications and systems
examples: The programmer debugged the code to fix the application crashes
Our team needs an experienced programmer familiar with cloud computing

definitions: process of developing or moving gradually towards a more advanced state or condition
examples: The patient's progression toward recovery exceeded the doctor's expectations completely
Musical progression from basic chords to complex harmonies takes practice

definitions: political and social philosophy advocating for reform, modernization, and advancement of human conditions through government action
examples: Early twentieth-century progressivism led to significant labor law reforms nationwide
The candidate's progressivism appealed to voters seeking systemic social changes

definitions: action of formally forbidding something by law, rule, or authority
period in United States history when alcohol production and sale was illegal
examples: The prohibition of smoking in public buildings improved air quality

Prohibition lasted from 1920 to 1933 in the United States
Speakeasies operated secretly during Prohibition despite law enforcement efforts

definitions: person who supports or advocates for prohibiting something, especially the sale of alcohol
examples: The prohibitionist movement gained momentum through grassroots organizing efforts nationwide
Local prohibitionists petitioned the city council to ban liquor stores

definitions: object that is thrown, fired, or otherwise propelled through space or air
examples: The physics class calculated the trajectory of various projectiles launched
Ancient warriors used stones and arrows as deadly projectiles in battle

definitions: person who operates movie projectors in theaters to display films for audiences
examples: The projectionist ensured the film reels were properly threaded before showtime

definitions: device that projects images or videos onto a screen or surface for viewing
examples: The teacher used a projector to display the presentation slides
We need a new projector for the conference room meetings

definitions: medical condition where an organ falls or slips from its normal position in the body
examples: The doctor diagnosed a mild prolapse requiring physical therapy treatment
Pelvic floor exercises can help prevent prolapse after childbirth recovery

definitions: member of the working class, especially industrial wage earners who lack property or capital

definitions: collective term for workers or working-class people regarded as a social group, especially in Marxist theory
examples: The proletariat organized strikes to demand better working conditions nationwide
Revolutionary leaders called upon the proletariat to overthrow oppressive systems

definitions: rapid increase in numbers or spread of something, often in an uncontrolled manner
examples: The proliferation of smartphones changed how people communicate and work
Scientists worry about the proliferation of antibiotic-resistant bacteria in hospitals

definitions: separate introductory section of a literary work or performance that provides context or background
examples: The novel's prologue revealed events that occurred twenty years earlier
Shakespeare often used prologues to set the scene for audiences

definitions: act of making something last longer or extending its duration beyond the original timeframe
examples: The prolongation of negotiations frustrated both parties seeking quick resolution
Medical treatment resulted in prolongation of the patient's life expectancy

definitions: formal dance event for high school students, typically held near the end of the academic year
examples: She spent months searching for the perfect dress to wear to prom
The prom committee decorated the gymnasium with twinkling lights and balloons

definitions: paved public walkway, typically along a waterfront or in a park
leisurely walk taken in a public place for pleasure or display
examples: Tourists strolled along the seaside promenade enjoying ocean views

Their evening promenade through the gardens became a cherished ritual
Victorian couples would promenade to see and be seen socially

definitions: state of being important, famous, or noticeable in a particular sphere or profession
examples: The scientist rose to prominence after her groundbreaking cancer research
The building's prominence on the skyline makes it a landmark

definitions: practice of engaging in sexual activity frequently with different partners or being indiscriminate in choice
examples: The health class discussed risks associated with promiscuity among teenagers
Victorian society harshly judged any hint of promiscuity in women

definitions: short promotional film, advertisement, or announcement designed to advertise something
examples: The band released a promo video to generate excitement for their tour

definitions: high point of land or rock projecting into water or prominent above surrounding lowland
examples: The lighthouse stands on a rocky promontory overlooking the harbor
From the promontory, hikers enjoyed panoramic views of the coastline

definitions: person or company that finances or organizes sporting events, concerts, or other entertainment
person who actively supports or encourages something to happen or develop
examples: The concert promoter booked venues and handled ticket sales nationwide

definitions: act of encouraging or reminding someone to do something or say something
examples: The teacher's gentle prompting helped the shy student answer questions

definitions: formal public announcement or declaration of a new law, policy, or decree by an authority
examples: The promulgation of new regulations affected all financial institutions immediately

definitions: pointed projecting part, especially each pointed tip of a fork or similar implement
examples: One prong of the fork bent when he tried to open the jar

definitions: three-dimensional spiral curve, especially the shape of DNA molecules or spiral staircases
examples: The DNA double helix contains genetic information in living organisms
The staircase followed a helix pattern ascending the lighthouse tower

definitions: relating to ancient or modern Greece, its people, language, or culture
examples: The museum's Hellenic collection includes pottery from ancient Athens
Hellenic studies programs explore Greek philosophy, literature, and history

definitions: widely used sans-serif typeface developed in Switzerland, known for its clean, modern appearance
examples: The designer chose Helvetica font for the company's minimalist logo

definitions: long-legged freshwater and coastal bird with long neck and bill for catching fish
examples: A great blue heron stood motionless waiting for fish to swim by
The heron spread its wide wings and flew across the marsh

definitions: German title of respect equivalent to Mister, used before a man's surname
examples: Herr Schmidt will conduct the orchestra at tonight's performance in Berlin
